body.\\n\\n`initGame()`: Initializes the game by setting up the game board, loading the necessary images, and starting the game timer.\\n\\n`loadImages()`: Loads the images used in the game, such as the snake\\u0027s body, head, and the apple.\\n\\n`initBoard()`: Initializes the game board by setting the initial position of the snake and the location of the first apple.\\n\\n`paintComponent(Graphics g)`: Draws the current state of the game on the game board.\\n\\n`gameOver(Graphics g)`: Displays the \\\"Game Over\\\" message when the player loses the game.\\n\\n`move()`: Updates the position of the snake\\u0027s body based on the current direction.\\n\\n`checkApple()`: Checks if the snake\\u0027s head has collided with the apple, and if so, increases the length of the snake and spawns a new apple.\\n\\n`checkCollision()`: Checks if the snake has collided with the walls or its own body, and if so, sets the `inGame` flag to `false`.\\n\\n`locateApple()`: Randomly generates a new location for the apple on the game board.\\n\\n`actionPerformed(ActionEvent e)`: Handles the game logic, including moving the snake, checking for collisions, and updating the game state.\\n\\n`TAdapter`: A private inner class that extends `KeyAdapter` and handles the player\\u0027s keyboard input to control the snake\\u0027s movement.\\n\\n`restartGame()`: Resets the game state and starts a new game when the player presses the Space key.\\n\\n`main(String[] args)`: The main entry point of the application, which creates a new `JFrame` and adds the `SnakeGame` instance to it.\",\"/BaiTapB6QLNV.java\":\"This file is a Java Swing application for managing employee information. It has the following classes and functions:\\n\\n`NhanVien`: A class that represents an employee with properties such as employee ID, name, age, email, and basic salary.\\n\\n`main`: The main entry point of the application, which creates a GUI window with various input fields, buttons, and a table to display the list of employees.\\n\\nThe application allows users to perform the following operations:\\n- Add a new employee\\n- Export the list of employees to a text file\\n- Delete an employee by their ID\\n- Update an employee\\u0027s information\\n- Search for an employee by their ID\\n\\nThe application also includes input validation to ensure that the user enters valid data, and displays appropriate error messages if any issues are encountered.\",\"/UDChuyenDoiPNG.java\":\"This file contains a single class `UDChuyenDoiPNG` that provides a graphical user interface (GUI) application for converting image files to the PNG format.\\n\\n`UDChuyenDoiPNG`: A GUI application that allows users to select an image file, choose a location to save the converted PNG file, and perform the conversion.\\n\\n`checkReadyToConvert()`: A method that checks if the user has selected an input file and output location, and enables the \\\"Convert\\\" button accordingly.\\n\\n`convertToPNG(File, File)`: A method that reads the input image file, converts it to PNG format, and saves the resulting file to the specified output location.\\n\\n`main(String[])`: The main entry point of the application, which creates and displays the `UDChuyenDoiPNG` GUI.\",\"/BaiTapB8QLNVv2.java\":\"This file is a Java Swing application for managing employee information. It allows users to perform various operations such as adding, deleting, updating, and searching employees, as well as importing and exporting employee data to/from CSV files. The application also includes features like generating random employee data and randomly selecting employees for rewards.\\n\\n`NhanVien`: A class representing an employee with properties such as employee ID, name, age, email, and base salary.\\n\\n`importFromCSV`: A function that imports employee data from a CSV file and returns a list of `NhanVien` objects.\\n\\n`exportToCSV`: A function that exports a list of `NhanVien` objects to a CSV file.\\n\\n`generateRandomEmployeeList`: A function that generates a random list of employees and exports it to a CSV file.\\n\\n`main`: The main entry point of the application, which sets up the Swing GUI and handles the various user interactions.\",\"/BaiTapB7LotteryApp.java\":\"This file is a Java Swing application that simulates a lottery game. When a button is clicked, the corresponding number label starts cycling through random numbers, simulating a lottery draw.\",\"/BaiTapB4Xfile.java\":\"This file contains a single class `BaiTapB4Xfile` Closes the database connection, statement, and result set.\",\"/CtyRongVietV2.java\":\"This file is a Java Swing application that manages a list of employees in a company called \\\"Cty Rong Viet\\\". It allows the user to add, view, search, update, and sort the employees based on their information.\\n\\n`NhanVienCty`: An abstract class that represents a company employee and provides a common interface for calculating their income.\\n\\n`NhanVienHanhChinh`: A concrete implementation of `NhanVienCty` that represents an administrative employee with a base salary and number of working days.\\n\\n`NhanVienKinhDoanh`: A concrete implementation of `NhanVienCty` that represents a sales employee with a base salary and sales commission.\\n\\n`main`: The entry point of the application, which creates the main window and sets up the user interface with various buttons and functionality.\",\"/B11QLNV/src/main/java/org/example/MainQLNV.java\":\"This file is a Java Swing application for managing employee information. It includes the following classes and functions:\\n\\n`MainQLNV`: The main class that sets up the Swing GUI and handles the various functionalities of the application.\\n\\n`NhanVien`: A class that represents an employee with properties such as employee ID, name, age, email, and salary.\\n\\n`loadnv()`: A function that loads the employee data from a MySQL database and displays it in the table.\\n\\n`importFromCSV(File file)`: A function that imports employee data from a CSV file and inserts it into the MySQL database.\\n\\n`laydanhsachtuDB()`: A function that retrieves the list of employees from the MySQL database and returns it as a list of `NhanVien` objects.\\n\\n`exportToCSV(File file, List\\u003cNhanVien\\u003e danhSach)`: A function that exports the list of employees to a CSV file.\\n\\n`generateRandomEmployeeList(File file, int soLuong)`: A function that generates a random list of employees and writes it to a CSV file.\",\"/B9ORM/src/main/java/org/example/student.java\":\"`student`: A class that represents a student, with an ID and a name.\\n\\n`getId()`: Returns the ID of the student.\\n`setId(int id)`: Sets the ID of the student.\\n`getName()`: Returns the name of the student.\\n`setName(String name)`: Sets the name of the student.\\n\\nThis file defines a `student` class with private instance variables for the student\\u0027s ID and name, and provides getter and setter methods to access and modify these values.\",\"/Games/GameXepHinh.java\":\"This file contains a single class `GameXepHinh` that implements a Tetris-like game using Java Swing. The game board is represented as a 2D boolean array, and the game logic is handled through various methods that control the movement and rotation of the falling blocks, as well as the clearing of completed lines and the updating of the game score and speed.\\n\\n`GameXepHinh`: A Tetris-like game that allows the player to control the movement and rotation of falling blocks to clear lines and earn points.\\n\\n`mergeToBoard()`: Merges the current block with the game board and clears any completed lines.\\n\\n`clearLines()`: Checks the game board for completed lines and removes them, updating the score and game speed accordingly.\\n\\n`removeLine(int row)`: Removes a single line from the game board by shifting all the rows above it down.\\n\\n`paintComponent(Graphics g)`: Draws the current game state, including the falling block and the fixed blocks on the board, as well as the current score and speed.\\n\\n`actionPerformed(ActionEvent e)`: Handles the game logic, moving the falling block down and checking for collisions, resetting the block when necessary, and ending the game if the player loses.\\n\\n`keyPressed(KeyEvent e)`: Handles user input, allowing the player to move the falling block left, right, or down, and to rotate the block.\\n\\n`resetGame()`: Resets the game board and game state to the initial conditions, allowing the player to start a new game.\\n\\n`rotate()` and `rotateBack()`: Rotate the current block and its corresponding positions on the game board.\\n\\n`initV()`: Initializes the vector of squares that make up the current falling block based on the block type.\\n\\n`getColorByType(int type)`: Returns the color to be used for the current falling block based on its type.\"}"}
